Former governor of Adamawa State, Umar Bindow, has formally declared his ambition to contest the gubernatorial seat of the state in 2023. Bindow who made his intention known at the APC Secretariat Yola, admitted making mistakes during his administration and also sought forgiveness from his supporters and the party. He asked the people of Adamawa to give him a second chance to complete his pending dividend of democracy to the people of the state. He said his administration had executed 387 roads and bridges promising to do more for the state. Bindow prevailed on other aspirants to step down for him even as he promised to retain Marthins Babale as his deputy in the contest. The state chairman of APC, Alhaji Ibrahim Bilal, appealed to party supporters to dislodge PDP government in the state by voting APC back to power again. 